description: TEHRAN – Persepolis football team defeated Shams Azar 3-1 in their away match and need just one victory to win the 2023/24 Iran’s Persian Gulf Pro League (PGPL) on Tuesday.
title: Persepolis one step away from PGPL title after win over Shams Azar

description: TEHRAN – Sanat Naft football team were relegated at the end of the 2023/24 Iran’s Persian Gulf Pro League (PGPL).
title: Sanat Naft relegated from 2023/24 PGPL

description: TEHRAN- Israel’s weekend brutal attack on a tent camp in Gaza’s southernmost city of Rafah has sparked global outrage and anti-war protests across the world.
title: Global protests condemn Israeli carnage in Rafah

description: TEHRAN - In its editorial, Siasat-e-Rooz analyzed Biden's confession that Iran's missile and drone attack was devastating and wrote: First of all, this confession is another proof of the falsity of the previous claims of the Zionists and the United States.
title: Biden admits inability of sanctions

description: TEHRAN – Three traditional dolls from Qazvin province have been officially recognized as intangible cultural heritage, highlighting the region’s rich cultural tapestry.
title: Qazvin’s traditional dolls join national intangible legacy

description: TEHRAN- The 56th edition of the Persian translation of Portuguese writer José Saramago’s 1995 novel “Blindness” has recently been published.
title: Persian edition of “Blindness” republished

description: TEHRAN- Renowned Iranian vocalist Alireza Ghorbani is set to give a concert at the prestigious Dubai Opera on June 7.
title: Iranian vocalist Alireza Ghorbani to perform in Dubai

description: TEHRAN - In a strongly worded letter to the Iranian Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Kazem Gharib Abadi, Secretary of the High Council for Human Rights, has called for the immediate repatriation of an autistic Iranian child from Denmark.
title: Iran demands Denmark's cooperation in returning autistic child to family

description: TEHRAN - The Iranian Army Ground Force is embarking on a comprehensive plan to modernize and upgrade its arsenal using cutting-edge technologies developed domestically, according to a high-ranking commander.
title: Iran to modernize homegrown weapons

description: TEHRAN – The office of the late Ebrahim Raisi, Iran’s president who lost his life during a helicopter crash on May 19, has expressed appreciation at people’s large turnout at funeral processions held in major Iranian cities last week.
title: Late President’s office thanks Iranian nation for outpour of grief

description: TEHRAN – The warm reception given to Iraqi Prime Minister Mohammed Shia' Al Sudani in Tehran underscores the profound and enduring relationship between the Islamic Republic of Iran and Iraq, according to Hussein Alawi, an advisor to the Iraqi Prime Minister.
title: Tehran's warm welcome highlights deep Iran-Iraq ties: Iraqi official

description: TEHRAN – French President Emmanuel Macron has conveyed his condolences to Mohammad Mokhber, the acting President of Iran, in the wake of the tragic death of President Ebrahim Raisi and his accompanying officials.
title: Macron offers condolences to Iran acting President following Raisi's Passing

description: TEHRAN – American media platforms have once again targeted accounts affiliated with Iranian officials and organizations, with YouTube removing the channel of the Iranian Foreign Ministry on Tuesday.
title: YouTube shuts down Iranian Foreign Ministry channel

description: TEHRAN - Known as the ‘Lost Paradise of Khuzestan,’ Shimbar plain is a protected natural haven boasting stunning landscapes, diverse wildlife, and rich historical significance.
title: Shimbar plain: lost paradise of Khuzestan

description: TEHRAN - Abyaneh village in Isfahan, central Iran, is set to evolve into an event-focused destination.
title: Abyaneh village to embrace event-driven development

description: TEHRAN - Shah Abbasi Caravanserai in Karaj, northcentral Iran, a historic gem tracing back to the Safavid era, has reopened its gates after a four-year hiatus, to host a handicrafts, souvenirs, and food exhibition.
title: Shah Abbasi Caravanserai reopens after four years to host handicrafts exhibition

description: TEHRAN – During the past week, the streets of Kashmir witnessed a series of mourning as a profound sorrow took hold of the region. The news of Iran's President Ebrahim Raisi's tragic death in a helicopter crash has sent ripples of grief and sympathy across the area.
title: Kashmir mourns death of Iranian President Raisi

description: TEHRAN - Iran's Acting Foreign Minister, Ali Baqeri Kani, met with former Iraqi Prime Minister Adel Abdul-Mahdi in Tehran on Monday night. Abdul-Mahdi had traveled to Iran to pay his respects to the late President Ebrahim Raisi and Foreign Minister Hossein Amir Abdollahian, who lost their lives during a helicopter crash on May 19.
title: Iran's acting foreign minister meets with former Iraqi PM

description: TEHRAN- Secretary General of Lebanon’s Hezbollah resistance movement Sayyed Hassan Nasrallah said late on Tuesday that Israel’s airstrike against displaced Palestinians in Rafah has turned the spotlight on the extreme brutality of Zionists (the Israeli regime).
title: Hezbollah chief condemns Israeli “savage” attack in Rafah

description: TEHRAN - The Yemeni Ansarullah government has launched a wave of military operations in response to the recent Israeli massacre in Rafah.
title: Yemenis attack Israeli and U.S. ships

description: TEHRAN - Feeling that Israel is being badly isolated, Israeli Foreign Minister Israel Katz made a strong criticism of Spanish Prime Minister Pedro Sanchez over recognizing Palestine as a sovereign and independent state, claiming he is a “partner to incitement” of Jewish “genocide”.
title: Israel Katz resorting to deceitful and misleading remarks

description: TEHRAN - Three European countries on Tuesday formally recognized Palestine as a state, throwing a spotlight on the fact that the Palestinian struggle for statehood and self-determination remains a powerful and influential force on the international stage.
title: The fruit of resistance: Towards a Palestinian state

description: Throughout the 235 days of the ongoing Israeli genocide in Gaza, the Israeli occupation has deliberately targeted and assassinated dozens of Palestinian scholars, scientists, academics and researchers along with their families. All were targeted while at home with their families or seeking refuge with relatives. Last week, the Gaza media office released a list containing the names of 100 Palestinian researchers who the Israeli occupation has killed, including scientists, university professors and doctors.
title: The slaughter of Palestinian scholars in Gaza is a deliberate Israeli tactic

description: The BRICS+ International School of Basic and Supplementary Education and the BRICS+ Children's Camp of the same name have started operating in Moscow. Schoolchildren will acquire a wide range of skills: from public speaking to logistics market research, from effective negotiations to peacemaking diplomacy.
title: BRICS, IYC to focus on developing educational tourism in Russia

description: TEHRAN – In the first 2 months of the current Iranian calendar year which started on March 20, some 9.2 million tons of goods have been transited via the country’s roads, IRNA reported.
title: Over 9m tons of goods transited via roads since mid-March

description: TEHRAN - Russian Consul General in Isfahan Andrey Zhiltsov has highlighted the need to increase the trade volume between Iran and Russia, saying the current trade volume does not live up to the capacities.
title: Russia underscores need for enhanced trade with Iran

description: TEHRAN – Iran exported 1,562,000 tons of agricultural products worth $684 million since the beginning of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20) to May 20, an increase of 28 percent in value year on year.
title: Agrofood exports increase 28% in two months yr/yr

description: TEHRAN – Iran and Oman have untapped economic potential which they can use to multiply their economic and trade relations, Acting President Mohammad Mokhber has said.
title: ‘Tehran, Muscat have potential to multiply trade’

description: Modern methods of teaching Russian language and literature were discussed by the participants of the fourth Kostomarov Forum, where 116 countries were represented. Its programme included more than 30 events: panel discussions, seminars, conferences, master classes, creative meetings with writers, presentations of new projects and modern research.
title: Scholars, methodologists and teachers from 116 countries take part in Kostomarov Forum

description: TEHRAN –The implementation of a child care nutrition program has led to a 40-percent reduction in malnutrition among children under five years of age, according to an official with the health ministry.
title: Malnutrition among children under 5 drops by 40%

description: TEHRAN –Three Iranian scholars won Life-time Contribution Award in physics, and mathematics, as well as the Best Patent Award of the Organization of Islamic Cooperation (OIC) Standing Committee on Scientific and Technological Cooperation (COMSTECH) in 2023.
title: Iranian scholars grab COMSTECH awards

description: TEHRAN – The Islamic World Science Citation Center (ISC) has released the ranking of universities by subject 2023 according to which 43 universities from Iran are among the top 239 universities from Islamic nations.
title: ISC WUR by subject includes 43 Iranian Universities

description: TEHRAN –Health Minister Bahram Einollahi is participating in the 77th World Health Assembly (WHA) which is being held in Geneva, Switzerland, from May 27 to June 1.
title: Health minister attending 77th World Health Assembly

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s first Olympics gold medal winner Habibi celebrated his 93rd birthday on Monday, May 27.
title: Iran’s first Olympics gold medal winner Habibi turns 93

description: TEHRAN - Aytak Salamat scored a massive 26 points on Tuesday afternoon to help Iran complete a 3-1 match (26-24, 26-24, 19-25, 25-19) against Hong Kong in the 2024 AVC Challenge Cup  for Women.
title: Iran beat Hong Kong 2024 AVC Challenge Cup for Women

description: TEHRAN - It has been more than two months since Iran's last game in the FIBA 2025 Asia Cup Qualifiers, and the national team still don't have a new head coach.
title: Iran basketball federation weighing up candidates: official

description: TEHRAN – Neda Shahsavari and Mahdi Olfati have been chosen to carry Iran’s flag at the Opening Ceremony of the Paris 2024 Olympic Games.
title: Shahsavari, Olfati named Iran’s flag-bearers for 2024 Olympic Games

description: TEHRAN – Mohammad Bagher Qalibaf was elected overwhelmingly on Tuesday as the speaker of the new Iranian parliament, securing 198 votes in the 290-seat parliament.
title: Ghalibaf elected speaker in new parliament
